text: Richard Tritschler (September 10, 1883 - November 15, 1954) was an American gymnast. He competed in three events at the 1904 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1883 births Category:1954 deaths Category:American male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of the United States Category:Gymnasts at the 1904 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from St. Louis
